Highest-priority comment: The lock delay timer is being incremented in two places in game.js (inside the gravity/drop block and again in the on-ground block), which can cause pieces to lock faster than intended and inconsistently, especially at higher levels. This violates expected Tetris behavior and can make gameplay feel unfair.

How to fix:
- Only manage the lock delay timer in one place: the on-ground section. Remove any lockTimer increments from the gravity/drop branch. Also avoid force-starting the timer in inputSoftDrop; let the on-ground logic handle it uniformly.

Concrete changes:
1) In game.js, in update(dt), replace the gravity section with:
- If gravity move succeeds, reset lockTimer to 0.
- If gravity move fails, do not touch lockTimer here; let the on-ground section handle it.

